1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,633
<i> Mookie!</i>

2
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:13,733
<i> Poor you.</i>

3
00:00:13,867 --> 00:00:15,300
<i>It looks like no one
is taking care of you.</i>

4
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:16,467
<i> Don't worry.</i>

5
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:17,833
<i> I'll help you.</i>

6
00:00:17,967 --> 00:00:19,767
<i> This is my fault, Jade.</i>

7
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:22,367
<i>I didn't know how this happened,
Danilo.</i>

8
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,167
<i> I'm such a bad sister.</i>

9
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:25,400
<i> I'm so sorry.</i>

10
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:27,233
<i>I hope you can forgive me, Emma.</i>

11
00:00:27,367 --> 00:00:31,867
<i>Why don't you transfer her
to another psychiatric center?</i>

12
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,633
<i>Please don't bring me back
to Haven Wood.</i>

13
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,733
<i>They're making me crazy.
I won't get better.</i>

14
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:36,700
<i> On one condition...</i>

15
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:39,000
<i>You'll cooperate
with the treatment.</i>

16
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:42,133
<i>It looks like the fate
is playing tricks on you, Boss.</i>

17
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:43,533
<i> I don't care</i>

18
00:00:43,667 --> 00:00:46,000
<i>if that's the man Jade
is going crazy for right now.</i>

19
00:00:46,133 --> 00:00:49,867
<i> What matters to me is Emma.</i>

20
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,433
<i>Won't you tell them Emma's
staying at your house?</i>

21
00:00:52,567 --> 00:00:55,033
<i>Staying with me is what's best
for Emma.</i>

22
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:02,833
Well, Emma, Logan...

23
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:06,200
I have some wonderful news
to share.

24
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:08,867
After six months of dedicated
treatment,

25
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,233
therapy, and perseverance,

26
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:14,500
I am delighted to announce
that Emma

27
00:04:14,633 --> 00:04:15,933
has had an extraordinary
recovery

28
00:04:16,067 --> 00:04:19,133
from her psychiatric
illness.

29
00:04:19,267 --> 00:04:23,367
You're getting back to normal,
Emma.

30
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:27,267
Are you sure, Doc?

31
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,667
Yes, Logan. Look at this.

32
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:38,600
Emma demonstrated significant
progress in managing

33
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:42,833
her symptoms and enhancing
her coping mechanisms.

34
00:04:44,133 --> 00:04:47,933
That won't happen if Emma
didn't help herself.

35
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:53,533
Well...

36
00:04:53,667 --> 00:04:55,033
what can I say?

37
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:58,133
I'm not surprised.

38
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:00,400
Doc, thank you.

39
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:02,833
Emma, did you hear that?

40
00:05:03,933 --> 00:05:04,933
You're now healed.

41
00:05:05,967 --> 00:05:09,400
I won't get better
without your support.

42
00:05:09,533 --> 00:05:11,267
Thank you, Logan.

43
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,400
Thank you so much.

44
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:25,667
Always happy to help.

45
00:05:44,467 --> 00:05:46,200
You see?

46
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:51,067
You will never see that
smile in my old photos.

47
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,567
Why?

48
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:57,333
It's only now that I experience
having a complete

49
00:05:57,467 --> 00:05:58,733
and happy family.

50
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:06,333
Danilo and Mookie have fulfilled
that dream of mine.

51
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:12,800
So it's just right that I
removed Emma from their lives.

52
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:37,767
Such a beautiful, happy family.

53
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:43,100
The baby is my Maria Angela.

54
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:49,000
The father is Danilo.

55
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,867
But who's the mother?

56
00:06:59,733 --> 00:07:04,100
Of course, it's Olive.

57
00:07:07,467 --> 00:07:10,867
My one big happy family.

58
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:14,733
Do you agree?

59
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:20,067
Wow.

60
00:07:20,933 --> 00:07:22,267
You treat me to a good snack.

61
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,433
Sorry for this small treat.

62
00:07:25,567 --> 00:07:27,233
This is what I can only afford.

63
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:33,500
Logan, thank you for all
your help.

64
00:07:33,633 --> 00:07:36,467
I would probably have gone
completely crazy

65
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,300
if it weren't for you.

66
00:07:38,433 --> 00:07:39,500
It's okay.

67
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:41,033
The fishball is good.

68
00:07:42,067 --> 00:07:42,867
Really?

69
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,033
Yeah.

70
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:47,400
Danilo and I often go on dates
in stalls like this.

71
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:48,900
And when I was pregnant...

72
00:07:49,033 --> 00:07:51,233
When I was pregnant with Kyla,
Mookie.

73
00:07:52,367 --> 00:07:53,467
Sorry.

74
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,000
It's okay.

75
00:07:57,933 --> 00:07:59,567
Not a day goes by that you don't
talk about your husband

76
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:00,600
and child.

77
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:04,000
I wonder how they're doing.

78
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,800
I wonder how my husband
and daughter are doing.

79
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,500
Can I see them?

80
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:46,933
Emma, I don't think
this is the right time.

81
00:08:49,167 --> 00:08:50,633
But I'm all better now, Logan.

82
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:52,267
I'm healed.

83
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,433
I can finally face them now.

84
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:57,267
I'm no longer a burden
to our family.

85
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,767
I miss them so much.

86
00:09:17,233 --> 00:09:18,300
Be quiet.

87
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:20,467
Go on, Dan, keep on walking.

88
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,933
What's this?

89
00:09:22,067 --> 00:09:23,633
Where are you taking me?

90
00:09:23,767 --> 00:09:27,233
Just continue walking.
I'm sure you'll like this.

91
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,333
Careful.

92
00:09:28,467 --> 00:09:29,367
There's a big...

93
00:09:30,433 --> 00:09:31,067
Okay.

94
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,367
There you go.

95
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,600
Just a few more steps.

96
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:37,767
Just a little more. Okay.

97
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,933
Then sit down.

98
00:09:40,067 --> 00:09:40,300
Sit down.

99
00:09:40,433 --> 00:09:41,100
Slowly.

100
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:46,800
Slowly. Careful. Sit down.
There.

101
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:50,033
What's this?

102
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:53,400
Dan, I have a surprise for you.

103
00:09:53,533 --> 00:09:56,133
But promise me that you'll never
look back.

104
00:09:56,267 --> 00:09:56,867
Okay?

105
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:57,867
Okay, I won't.

106
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:58,667
Promise?

107
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:00,600
Promise.

108
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:01,533
Wait.

109
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:10,267
Okay.

110
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:12,567
Surprise!

111
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:18,400
You stop there.

112
00:10:18,533 --> 00:10:19,467
Surprise!

113
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,000
Why are there so many people
here?

114
00:10:21,133 --> 00:10:25,100
You didn't tell me that you'd
throw a party.

115
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:27,900
It's because I have a surprise
for you.

116
00:10:28,033 --> 00:10:30,733
I'm sure you'll like this, Dan.

117
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,200
So, everyone.

118
00:10:36,667 --> 00:10:40,400
Thank you so much
for being here.

119
00:10:41,533 --> 00:10:44,333
Thank you so much for coming.

120
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:48,200
Gosh!

121
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:51,433
I'm nervous!

122
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:56,833
Rush me to the hospital if
Danilo won't give a good answer.

123
00:10:56,967 --> 00:10:57,900
Okay?

124
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:07,633
Dan, I've been dreaming
of having my own family.

125
00:11:08,967 --> 00:11:16,533
But those darn boys fooled
and left me.

126
00:11:16,667 --> 00:11:23,700
So, I just accepted that maybe
I'll grow old alone.

127
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:25,300
But you know what?

128
00:11:26,867 --> 00:11:30,500
Everything has changed
since I met you and Mookie.

129
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:35,767
I get hurt when you
two get hurt.

130
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,567
I feel even worse.

131
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:44,600
So now, I want to fill in
whatever's missing

132
00:11:44,767 --> 00:11:46,200
in your and Mookie's life.

133
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:51,700
I want to fulfill your dream
of having a complete family.

134
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,567
And you know what, Dan?

135
00:11:56,233 --> 00:11:59,433
I can't imagine starting
a family with anyone

136
00:11:59,567 --> 00:12:00,800
but you and Mookie.

137
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:05,700
So, Dan...

138
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:13,433
Will you marry me?

139
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:18,233
Hey, Jade.

140
00:12:21,733 --> 00:12:26,200
Dan, will you take this journey
with me?

141
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:30,000
And will you let Mookie
and us be a family?

142
00:12:35,033 --> 00:12:37,767
Will you marry me, Dan?

143
00:12:50,467 --> 00:12:52,800
Will you marry me, Dan?

144
00:12:53,767 --> 00:12:55,267
Will you marry me?

145
00:12:58,033 --> 00:12:58,867
Dan...

146
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:02,600
Why is he taking so long
to answer?

147
00:13:02,733 --> 00:13:04,033
Come on!

148
00:13:07,767 --> 00:13:08,700
Yes, Jade.

149
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:10,100
Yes?

150
00:13:10,233 --> 00:13:11,833
I will marry you.

151
00:13:11,967 --> 00:13:13,033
Really?

152
00:13:15,133 --> 00:13:17,800
Keep this.
This is our wedding ring.

153
00:13:17,933 --> 00:13:20,000
Oh, Dan!

154
00:13:23,933 --> 00:13:25,500
My fiancé!

155
00:13:25,633 --> 00:13:28,300
I can't believe it!

156
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:30,200
I'm so happy!

157
00:13:30,333 --> 00:13:32,267
Thank you so much for saying
yes.

158
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:33,333
Congrats.

159
00:13:33,467 --> 00:13:34,833
I'm happy for both of you.

160
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:37,267
Thank you, thank you.

161
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,967
Thank you so much.

162
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:39,767
Thank you.

163
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:41,267
Thank you for coming.

164
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,500
My fiancé!

165
00:13:44,633 --> 00:13:47,733
Mookie, are you okay?

166
00:13:47,867 --> 00:13:50,033
I don't know what to feel, Zayn.

167
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:55,133
I didn't expect that Aunt Jade
would propose to Dad.

168
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:59,967
I mean, I'm okay with Aunt Jade.

169
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:02,033
She has helped us a lot.

170
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:04,067
But...

171
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:08,767
Something feels wrong.
It seems that I'm betraying Mom.

172
00:14:18,267 --> 00:14:19,267
Mom?

173
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:22,200
Mookie.

174
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,767
Zayn, wait.

175
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:30,700
Mookie!

176
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:31,900
What is it?

177
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,500
I think I saw Mom.

178
00:14:37,633 --> 00:14:39,400
Didn't you see her?

179
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:41,267
Are you sure it's Aunt Emma?

180
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:47,567
Maybe I was just mistaken.

181
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:51,767
She would've shown up
to me long ago if she wanted to.

182
00:14:53,133 --> 00:14:54,000
Sorry, Mookie.

183
00:14:58,067 --> 00:15:00,300
I don't know why I'm waiting.

184
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:05,333
And why I still hope
she'll return for me.

185
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:10,633
I hope she never shows up to me.

186
00:15:13,367 --> 00:15:14,267
Let's go, Zayn.

187
00:15:21,033 --> 00:15:22,733
Emma.

188
00:15:22,867 --> 00:15:24,667
What are you doing here?

189
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,233
Good thing I followed you.

190
00:15:27,567 --> 00:15:28,467
I got you.

191
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:38,833
Aunt Jade...

192
00:15:38,967 --> 00:15:39,633
Yeah?

193
00:15:39,767 --> 00:15:40,467
Dad...

194
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,833
Congrats.

195
00:15:43,367 --> 00:15:45,833
We're officially gonna be
a family.

196
00:15:45,967 --> 00:15:47,700
- Congrats.
- Congrats, Auntie.

197
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:49,433
Thank you guys for coming.

198
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,100
Go and eat with your friends.
You take care of them.

199
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:58,833
Cheers, everyone!

200
00:16:04,033 --> 00:16:06,500
I really thought it was Mom.

201
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:10,500
But it seems like I was
mistaken.

202
00:16:10,667 --> 00:16:13,767
Baby girl, sit down.

203
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:18,833
I'm sure you saw it wrong.

204
00:16:18,967 --> 00:16:20,633
We've been looking for
her for a long time now.

205
00:16:20,767 --> 00:16:22,500
And we can't find her.

206
00:16:22,633 --> 00:16:24,067
Well...

207
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:27,967
you can't find someone who
doesn't want to be found.

208
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:33,467
She would have approached you
if that was Emma.

209
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:36,833
She has no reason
not to show up.

210
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:39,900
Please!

211
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:44,300
Let's not ruin this night
because of Emma.

212
00:16:44,467 --> 00:16:47,500
She would've come back long ago
if she wanted to.

213
00:16:47,633 --> 00:16:49,167
But she didn't do that.

214
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:54,500
For all we know, she already has
another family.

215
00:16:54,633 --> 00:16:56,100
So, please.

216
00:16:56,233 --> 00:16:58,700
Let's forget about Emma.

217
00:16:58,833 --> 00:17:02,633
We're going to be
a family anyway.

218
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:06,533
I'm so happy.

219
00:17:13,467 --> 00:17:16,200
Jade, I'll just get some coffee.

220
00:17:16,367 --> 00:17:17,267
Go on.

221
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:18,333
I'll take care of everything
here.

222
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:19,433
Go get some rest.

223
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:22,500
- Bye.
- See you, love.

224
00:17:37,100 --> 00:17:39,067
Hello, Caloy.

225
00:17:41,067 --> 00:17:44,267
Are you sure you can't find
Emma?

226
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,500
<i> I'm sure, Ma'am.</i>

227
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,600
<i>She's probably in a faraway
province now.</i>

228
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,033
<i> Or if not, she's already dead.</i>

229
00:17:49,167 --> 00:17:50,767
Make sure of that.

230
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:54,033
She could really be the one
Mookie saw wandering

231
00:17:54,167 --> 00:17:55,833
around here.

232
00:17:57,767 --> 00:17:59,500
<i> Don't worry about that, Ma'am.</i>

233
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:01,000
<i>Emma won't be coming back there
anymore.</i>

234
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:17,467
It's so painful to hear that
Mookie's so upset with me.

235
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:20,000
We couldn't even talk.

236
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:21,033
I couldn't hug her.

237
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:23,700
I wasn't able to explain
everything to her.

238
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:27,200
Maybe that's what Danilo
and Jade told her.

239
00:18:27,333 --> 00:18:30,200
That's why she's upset with me.

240
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:33,733
I knew it.
Jade and Olive are the same.

241
00:18:33,867 --> 00:18:39,333
I'll give you a bonus if I am
satisfied with your job.

242
00:18:39,467 --> 00:18:40,400
I knew it, Madam.

243
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:44,167
You're as generous
as your sister.

244
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:47,600
She sent me to a mental hospital
to drive me crazy.

245
00:18:47,733 --> 00:18:51,233
I saw her talking to Andrea,
the nurse who watched me.

246
00:18:51,367 --> 00:18:54,367
They gave me the wrong
medications.

247
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:57,200
Because she planned
to steal my family.

248
00:18:57,367 --> 00:18:59,267
Jade fooled me.

249
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,100
And Danilo, too!

250
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:09,200
Emma, that's enough.

251
00:19:10,533 --> 00:19:11,900
Stop.

252
00:19:14,067 --> 00:19:17,233
She does bad things to you
because she knows you're weak.

253
00:19:17,367 --> 00:19:19,300
My family is taken away from me.

254
00:19:19,433 --> 00:19:21,167
And I can't do anything.

255
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:22,733
You can do something.

256
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:25,133
We can do something.

257
00:19:31,767 --> 00:19:34,333
I have no plans of getting even
with Jade.

258
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:42,167
But for you, we'll take revenge
against her.

259
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:47,033
You know Jade?

260
00:19:51,767 --> 00:19:52,533
Danilo,

261
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:55,633
I'm sorry for what I did.

262
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:58,833
I know you were surprised.

263
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:04,600
Yes, you surprised me, Jade.

264
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:12,200
I'll understand if you're having
doubts.

265
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:14,967
You can back out.

266
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:17,733
I'm okay.

267
00:20:20,867 --> 00:20:23,100
I'm used to being alone.

268
00:20:24,633 --> 00:20:28,067
I'm only thinking about you
and Mookie.

269
00:20:29,533 --> 00:20:32,267
I want you guys to be happy.

270
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:35,367
Jade, you've done so much
for Mookie and me.

271
00:20:36,467 --> 00:20:38,100
Yes, I was surprised.

272
00:20:38,233 --> 00:20:44,400
But that doesn't mean
I'll back out.

273
00:20:48,467 --> 00:20:50,167
You're going to marry me?

274
00:20:57,067 --> 00:20:59,100
It's not hard to love you.

275
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:04,700
Besides, Emma and I aren't
married.

276
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:06,833
So we can marry, Jade.

277
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:12,767
And Mookie longs for a mother's
love.

278
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:16,267
And if Emma can't give it
to her,

279
00:21:17,567 --> 00:21:20,467
I know you're the only one
who can.

280
00:21:23,533 --> 00:21:24,933
I promise you.

281
00:21:27,133 --> 00:21:28,600
I'll be a good mother.

282
00:21:29,933 --> 00:21:33,100
I'll learn everything
that Emma does.

283
00:21:33,233 --> 00:21:35,667
And if I can, I'll do more.

284
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:40,833
So I can be a good wife to you
and a good mother to Mookie.

285
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:02,233
I appreciate your care for me.

286
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:08,767
Shameless!

287
00:22:17,933 --> 00:22:19,867
I will fight back, Logan.

288
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,800
I'll prepare for our
confrontation.

289
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:26,667
And I'll make them feel
the pain I have right now.

290
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:29,900
You can't do that without any
skills.

291
00:22:30,033 --> 00:22:34,233
I will help you prepare
for your reunion.

292
00:22:34,367 --> 00:22:37,133
You'll return Emma to Danilo
and Mookie?

293
00:22:37,267 --> 00:22:39,167
They're family.

294
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:41,000
Emma's gone!

295
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:43,567
I'm now Danilo and Mookie's
family!

296
00:22:43,700 --> 00:22:46,567
We thought Jade
was a good person.

297
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,033
But she's worse.

298
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:52,100
It reminded me of Olive
when she yelled at me.

299
00:22:52,233 --> 00:22:53,933
That's how Olive was.

300
00:22:54,067 --> 00:22:55,900
Haven't you still found Emma?

301
00:22:56,033 --> 00:22:59,700
Make it quick because there's
another nuisance here.

302
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:08,333
She must not know that Olive
is still very much alive.

303
00:23:11,133 --> 00:23:12,733
You're Olive?
